---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Motherlabs — Ada"
  description="Ada translates what you want to build into something AI can build correctly. Built by Motherlabs — one person, ~400 iterations, the real thing."
>
  <Nav />

  <main>
    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="container">
        <h1 class="hero-headline">
          You know exactly<br />what you want to build.
        </h1>
        <p class="hero-sub">
          You just can't always say it in a way the AI won't misinterpret.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-actions">
          <a href="/start" class="btn-primary">Get started</a>
          <a href="/ada" class="btn-ghost">What is Ada? &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- The experience — no heading, just honest prose -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container container--prose">
        <p>
          You've been building with AI for a while. The output is good.
          The problem is you're doing something the tools don't acknowledge:
          holding the whole vision in your head, across every session,
          re-explaining the architecture, re-establishing what this thing is
          supposed to be.
        </p>
        <p>
          You know when it built the wrong thing.
          You just don't always have the words to say why
          in a way the next prompt won't misread.
          So you adjust. And adjust. And you start to wonder
          if the ceiling is you.
        </p>
        <p class="pull">It's not you. It's the missing layer.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="sep" aria-hidden="true">&#x25C8;</div>

    <!-- Ada enters — not as a product announcement, as relief -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container container--prose">
        <p class="intro">Ada is a semantic compiler.</p>
        <p>
          You tell it what you want to build &mdash; in whatever language you
          actually think in. No technical questions. No framework decisions.
          Ada figures out what it genuinely doesn't know and asks only that.
          Then it compiles your intent into governed artifacts and gives
          Claude Code something it cannot misinterpret.
        </p>
        <p>
          The constraints live in the artifacts.
          Not in the prompt. Not in your memory.
          Not in a chat history that degrades between sessions.
        </p>
        <p>
          Ada holds what the project is supposed to be.
          Claude Code builds against it.
          You stay at the level you actually operate.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="sep" aria-hidden="true">&#x25C8;</div>

    <!-- How it works — clean, no section header -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container container--prose">
        <ol class="pipeline" role="list">
          <li class="pipeline-step">
            <span class="step-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <p class="step-title">You describe what you want to build.</p>
              <p class="step-body">
                In plain language. At whatever level you think in.
                Ada doesn't ask about frameworks, patterns, or libraries.
              </p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="pipeline-step">
            <span class="step-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <p class="step-title">Ada asks only what it genuinely doesn't know.</p>
              <p class="step-body">
                Semantic questions, not technical ones.
                What does this need to be? What does it not?
                The minimum set. No more.
              </p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="pipeline-step">
            <span class="step-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <p class="step-title">Ada compiles your intent into a governed blueprint.</p>
              <p class="step-body">
                This is the artifact. It is authoritative.
                It persists across sessions.
                It is not a prompt. It is not a doc. It is a constraint.
              </p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="pipeline-step">
            <span class="step-num">04</span>
            <div>
              <p class="step-title">Claude Code builds against it.</p>
              <p class="step-body">
                Ada governs what can be built.
                Claude Code builds it.
                Nothing gets lost in translation.
              </p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="sep" aria-hidden="true">&#x25C8;</div>

    <!-- Lab signal -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container container--prose">
        <blockquote class="lab-quote">
          Built by one person who had this exact problem.
          ~400 iterations since late 2024.
          The real thing, not the pitch deck version.
        </blockquote>
        <a href="/lab" class="lab-link">About Motherlabs &rarr;</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Final CTA -->
    <section class="section section--cta">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="cta-label">Ready when you are.</p>
        <div class="cta-actions">
          <a href="/start" class="btn-primary">Get started</a>
          <a href="/ada" class="btn-ghost">Read about Ada &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .container {
    max-width: 72rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 clamp(1.5rem, 5vw, 4rem);
  }

  .container--prose {
    max-width: 44rem;
  }

  /* Hero */
  .hero {
    padding: 7rem 0 5rem;
  }

  .hero-headline {
    font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 5vw, 3.75rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .hero-sub {
    font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 2.5vw, 1.25rem);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin: 0 0 2.5rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    max-width: 32rem;
  }

  .hero-actions {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  /* Buttons */
  .btn-primary {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-bg);
    background-color: var(--color-accent);
    padding: 0.7rem 1.4rem;
    border-radius: 3px;
    transition: background-color 0.12s ease;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
  }

  .btn-primary:hover {
    background-color: var(--color-accent-hover);
    color: var(--color-bg);
  }

  .btn-ghost {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    transition: color 0.12s ease;
  }

  .btn-ghost:hover {
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  /* Sections */
  .section {
    padding: 5rem 0;
  }

  /* Prose */
  .section p {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
  }

  .section p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .pull {
    font-size: 1.1875rem !important;
    color: var(--color-text) !important;
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-top: 0.5rem !important;
  }

  .intro {
    font-size: 1.375rem !important;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text) !important;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem !important;
  }

  /* Separator */
  .sep {
    text-align: center;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--color-text-dim);
    padding: 0;
    user-select: none;
  }

  /* Pipeline */
  .pipeline {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .pipeline-step {
    display: flex;
    gap: 2rem;
    padding: 1.75rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .pipeline-step:last-child {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .step-num {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--color-text-dim);
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    padding-top: 0.2rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 1.75rem;
  }

  .step-title {
    font-size: 1rem !important;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text) !important;
    margin: 0 0 0.4rem !important;
    line-height: 1.4 !important;
  }

  .step-body {
    font-size: 0.9375rem !important;
    color: var(--color-text-muted) !important;
    margin: 0 !important;
    line-height: 1.65 !important;
  }

  /* Lab signal */
  .lab-quote {
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
    padding: 0;
    border: none;
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .lab-link {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--color-text-dim);
    transition: color 0.12s ease;
  }

  .lab-link:hover {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  /* Final CTA */
  .section--cta {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    padding: 4rem 0;
  }

  .cta-label {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text-dim);
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .cta-actions {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .hero {
      padding: 4.5rem 0 3.5rem;
    }

    .pipeline-step {
      gap: 1.25rem;
    }
  }
</style>
